  "text": "Pod security context field validation in kubernetes/kubernetes occurs at two main layers: (1) The **Pod Security Admission** plugin in `staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/policy/` implements policy checks as part of the Pod Security Standards (baseline/restricted). Each of the four requested checks has dedicated files: `check_runAsNonRoot.go` (enforces runAsNonRoot=true at restricted level), `check_privileged.go` (forbids privileged=true at baseline level), `check_capabilities_baseline.go` and `check_capabilities_restricted.go` (limit added capabilities at baseline, require dropping ALL at restricted), and `check_seccompProfile_baseline.go` and `check_seccompProfile_restricted.go` (restrict seccomp profile types). These checks are registered via `addCheck()` in `checks.go`, use `visitContainers()` from `visitor.go`, and are wired into the admission plugin via `plugin/pkg/admission/security/podsecurity/admission.go`. (2) The **core API validation** in `pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go` validates security context fields at API level, including the privileged flag against cluster capabilities, seccomp profile type/field validation, and capabilities interaction with allowPrivilegeEscalation. (3) The **kubelet runtime** layer in `pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/security_context_others.go` enforces `verifyRunAsNonRoot` at container start time, and `security_context.go` handles conversion of capabilities and privileged settings to the CRI runtime format.",
